ine withdrawal, primarily in patients who have received excessive doses over a prolonged period, may result in numbness and tingling of extremities, hypersensitivity to light and noise, hallucinations, and epileptic seizures.', 'Synergism', 'Amisulpride', 'Naltrexone, Acetaminophen, Ibuprofen, Celecoxib, Acetylsalicylic acid, Naloxone', 'Major', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/289779/', '[1] US Food and Drug Administration "FDA warns about serious risks and death when combining opioid pain or cough medicines with benzodiazepines; requires its strongest warning.  http://www.fda.gov/downloads/Drugs/DrugSafety/UCM518672.pdf"   (2016):', 1767369485);
INSERT OR REPLACE INTO drug_interactions (id, ingredient1, ingredient2, severity, effect, arabic_effect, recommendation, arabic_recommendation, management_text, mechanism_text, alternatives_a, alternatives_b, risk_level, ddinter_id, source, type, metabolism_info, source_url, reference_text, updated_at) VALUES (245850, 'Imatinib', 'Dihydrocodeine', 'Moderate', 'Coadministration with imatinib may increase the plasma concentrations of drugs that are substrates of CYP450 2C9, 2D6 and/or 3A4.  The mechanism is decreased clearance due to inhibition of these isoenzymes by imatinib.', NULL, 'Caution is advised when imatinib is used concomitantly with drugs that undergo metabolism by CYP450 2C9, 2D6 and/or 3A4, particularly those with a narrow therapeutic range.', NULL, 'Caution is advised when imatinib is used concomitantly with drugs that undergo metabolism by CYP450 2C9, 2D6 and/or 3A4, particularly those with a narrow therapeutic range.  Dosage adjustments as well as clinical and laboratory monitoring may be appropriate for some drugs whenever imatinib is added to or withdrawn from therapy.', 'Metabolism', 'Entrectinib, Acalabrutinib, Dacomitinib, Pexidartinib, Tepotinib, Avapritinib, Bosutinib, Vemurafenib, Selumetinib, Vandetanib, Cobimetinib, More', 'Tapentadol, Oxymorphone, Meperidine, Dezocine, Opium, Dextropropoxyphene, Pentazocine, Naloxone, Nalbuphine', 'Moderate', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/289780/', '[1] "Product Information. Gleevec (imatinib)." Novartis Pharmaceuticals  (2022):', 1767369485);
