sychoactive drugs.', 'Synergism', 'Ioxilan, Iodipamide, Ioversol, Iodamide, Iodixanol, Tyropanoic acid, Ethiodized oil, Iopanoic acid, Iopodic acid, Iothalamic acid, Ioxaglic acid, More', 'Acetylsalicylic acid, Acetaminophen, Naloxone, Naltrexone', 'Major', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/289784/', '[1] Hindmarsh T, Grepe A, Widen L "Metrizamide-phenothiazine interaction: report of a case with seizures following myelography." Acta Radiol Diagn (Stockh) 16 (1975):  129-35[2] "Product Information. Amipaque (metrizamide)." Nycomed Inc  (2001):[3] "Product Information. Osmovist 240 (iotrolan)." Berlex Canada Inc  (2001):[4] "Product Information. Omnipaque 180 (iohexol)." Amersham Health  (2007):[5] "Product Information. Isovue-M-200 (iopamidol)." Bracco Diagnostics Inc  (2007):', 1767369485);
